How to use build_book
=====================

Command options
---------------

  bin/build_book -h

Process
-------

  With thanks to mikekaganski of Freenode#libreoffice

  Run build_book

  Open LibreOffice Writer (or similar)

  1.      To convert the string '__page_break__' to an actual page break:
    1.1. The __page_break__ string should already start a new paragraph.
    1.2. Edit -> Find and Replace 
          Find:       __page_break__
          Find All
          Close
    1.3. Upper menu: Format -> Paragraph -> Text Flow
          "Breaks"    -> Insert
          "Type"      -> Page
          "Position"  -> Before
          "Ok"
    1.4.  Edit -> Find and Replace
          Find:       __page_break__
          Replace:    <leave empty>
          Replace All
          Close

  2.      To make the Chapter headers bold.
    2.1.  Edit -> Find and Replace
    2.2.  Find:     Chapter [:digit:]{3}
    2.3.  Format -> Font -> Style -> Bold
    2.4.  Replace:  &
    2.5.  Replace All
    2.6.  Repeat for "Prologue", "Epilogue", "Afterward", 
          and "Insider Information".
    2.7.  Close
    2.8.  Manually Bold and alter size on the Title and Dedication pages.

  3.      To make the Time_Location headers bold.
    3.1.  Edit -> Find and Replace
    3.2.  Find:     \[.*
    3.3.  Format -> Font -> Style -> Bold
    3.4.  Replace:  &
    3.5.  Replace All
    3.6.  Close

  4.      To select a font not on the list
    4.1.  Use either Garamond or Palatino
    4.2.  Ctrl-a to select all.
    4.3.  Type in the font name in the font entry.


